  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: `v2021.10.05`\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Linux Mint 20.2\r\n\r\nProbably related to #2888 \r\n\r\nMy erigon instance started throwing endless `MDBX_MAP_FULL` messages. I went back and looked at the logs and have attached them. I truncated the fluff and endlessly repeating messages.\r\n\r\nHere's what I see from the logs:\r\n\r\nNode processes some BAD BLOCKS and rewinds, this looks more or less normal, however, shortly after it hits `MDBX_MAP_FULL` errors at the `CallTraces` stage, then at the various other stages.\r\n\r\nI then later get an error `consensus.ErrUnknownAncestor`\r\n\r\nI restart the whole process and ergion is stuck with:\r\n> bucket: TxSender, mdbx_cursor_put: MDBX_MAP_FULL: Environment mapsize limit reached\r\n\r\nIn an endless loop.\r\n\r\n[erigon.err.log](https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/files/7532938/erigon.err.log)\r\n\r\n ",
